name: Burundi Gatara Masha
short_desc: Abundant sweetness at all roast levels, with hints of dried currant, jamaica tea, ginger powder, and candied lemon accenting aroma. Dark roasts are low toned with mild hints of fruit. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Burundi Kabarore Commune Yandaro
short_desc: Yandaro has caramel sugar sweetness at light roast levels accented by hints of apple, mild yellow tea, and zesty orange and lemon accents. Milky dark chocolate and a grape hint when roasted dark. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Burundi Kayanza Gakenke
short_desc: Gakenke treads familiar territory for Burundi coffee, substantial sweetness is accented by notes of black teas and spices, tangy lemon, Darjeeling tea, and aromatic accents of clove and bergamot citrus in the aftertaste. City to Full City.

name: Burundi Kayanza Kibingo Station
short_desc: Pour over brews highlight Kibingo's bright cup characteristics and clean raw sugar sweetness, along with flavor profiles of orange spice tea and tart jamaica, raw sugars, a spiced mixture of clove and mace, and cranberry-like acidity. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Burundi Kayanza Munkaze
short_desc: Impressive cup sweetness that deserves a high score on its own. Add in hints of honey glaze, cardamom and ginger powders, and a lemony citrus accent note, and we have ourselves a top-notch Burundi! City to Full City.

name: Congo Organic Kivu Kalehe
short_desc: We're pleased to broaden our origin representation with this fine example from Congo. Molasses, hints of malted grain, fruity tobacco, black tea, clove oil bittering, dark cocoa and a dried prune note. City to Full City+.

name: East Africa Sample Set: Rwanda & Burundi
short_desc: High caliber coffees in their own right, the East Africa Sample Set emphasizes flavor diversity found in the coffees from these two neighboring countries. Every coffee included in this set scores above 88 points, and two are fit for espresso too!Includes wet and dry process coffees from:Rwanda Dry Process MacubaRwanda Kivu KageyoBurundi Kayanza GakenkeBurundi Gatara Masha

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Buno Bobea
short_desc: Buno Bobea offers exotic fruit flavors, with syrupy sweetness, and flavor profiles of mixed fruit juice, berry, mango, stone fruit accents of dried apricot and peach along with moderate brightness when roasted light. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Idido Desalegn Hijo
short_desc: Fruit and honey cup flavors are a big part of the cup profile that is on the more refined end of the dry process spectrum. Aromatic stone fruits, dried blueberry, and a glazed orange peel note that adds to the acidic impression. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Kafa Dehab Mesfin Farm
short_desc: Delicious fruits and bittersweetness, notes of berry, cinnamon streusel, and floral accents. Also a syrupy textured espresso shot of inky dark chocolates with fruits underneath. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Mahamed Aba Nura
short_desc: Aromatic fruit, pronounced sweetness, and moderate acidic impression for dry process coffee. Notes of peach, apricot, lemon peel, with rustic hints of prune, date sugar, and cocoa with more roast. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Mansur Aba Hikam
short_desc: Lighter roasts promise an overlay of fruits and rustic sweeteners, bluberry, dried fig, maple, palm sugar, coconut date rolls, molasses, and a layer of chocolate bittersweets added in when roasted dark. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Senna Katta Mountain
short_desc: City+ roasts pull out a range of stone fruit flavors, rustic cocoa, and tart berry hints that add an acidic impression that's a nice addition for a fruity dry process coffee. A versatile dry process. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Guji Buku Sayisa
region: Buku Village, Hambela Wamena, Guji Zone
roast: City to City+ - the cracks are hardly audible, and best if you can watch for physical fracturing
short_desc: Atypical flavors for Guji, with a unique mix of herbal, forward facing fruit, and mild florals. Cantaloupe and galia melon, baked peach, miso, orange marmalade, pungent papaya, and jack fruit accent note. City to City+.*Please note the beans are very small (down to 13 screen) and dense, 1st Crack is subtle and hard to hear. See Farm Notes for roasting tips.

name: Ethiopia Kayon Mountain Taaroo
short_desc: Taaroo shows a delicate side that's tea-like, bright and distinct. It's the kind of profile you'd expect to make top placement in a coffee competition! Star jasmine, herbal rue, tart citrus, and passion fruit hints. City to City+.

name: Ethiopia Organic Dry Process Wolenso Dabessa
short_desc: Date sugar sweetness opens up to fruit flavors and cocoa bittersweets, dried apricot, tamarind, dehydrated strawberry, and raisin. Incredible dry process espresso option too (see review)! City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Organic Geta Bore Coop
short_desc: A dynamic cup profile with aromatic sweetness, sugar cane juice, ripe stone fruits, peach tea, mango, and fruit gum. A very friendly dark roast candidate too, not too bittersweet, and with a dark berry note. City to Full City+.

name: Ethiopia Sample Set: Dry Process Trio
short_desc: This sample set currently includes:Ethiopia Dry Process Kafa Dehab Mesfin Farm: Delicious fruits and bittersweetness, notes of berry, cinnamon streusel, and floral accents. Also a syrupy textured espresso shot of inky dark chocolates with fruits underneath. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.Ethiopia Dry Process Kata Senna Mountain: City+ roasts pull out a range of stone fruit flavors, rustic cocoa, and tart berry hints that add an acidic impression that's a nice addition for a fruity dry process coffee. A versatile dry process. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.Ethiopia Dry Process Wollenso Dabessa: Date sugar sweetness opens up to fruit flavors and cocoa bittersweets, dried apricot, tamarind, dehydrated strawberry, and raisin. Incredible dry process espresso option too (see review)! City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Kenya Nyeri Gatugi AA
short_desc: Fruits at the front of the cup, pomegranate, mixed berry, mulled grape juice, and citrus hints of citrus rind and lemonade enhance the bright acidity. Spiced accents lead to some woody incense in the finish. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Gichichi AB
short_desc: A vibrant and juicy cup at all roast levels we tried, with a fruited sweetness that's fortified by notes of dried cranberry, currant, blackberry compote, raw sugars, and a sweet/tart profile of elderberry tea. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Kagunyu AA
short_desc: Vibrant and sweet, with flavors of tangy lemon, brisk black tea, dried goji berry, rustic sugars, tamarind, coconut water, and delicious fruited-chocolate side when roasted to Full City. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Kamoini AB
short_desc: A delicious pour-over brew, with layered sweetness of simple syrup, toasted sugar, and corn syrup, citrus fruits that enhance a bright acidic impression, and a hop/spice hint that reminded me of Belgian white beer. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Kiaguthu AA
short_desc: A "light and bright" cup profile when kept to City-City+ roast levels. Tart lemon notes bring vivid acidity to the brew, and are buffered by cane sugar and berry, a combination that brought to mind cranberry lemonade. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Thunguri AB
short_desc: Light roasts bear tart fruits and sweetness that rides the line between fruit pectin and raw sugar, with notes of citrus, pomegranate, and spice. Full City develops a bittersweet layer that melds with dark berry notes. City to Full City.

name: Rwanda Dry Process Macuba
short_desc: Fruit-forward no matter what roast you throw at it; ripe blackberry, winey accents, chocolate-cherry cordials, fruit liqueur, and jam. A moderate acidity level helps prop up the wilder fruit flavors. City to Full City+.

name: Rwanda Honey Process Kanyege
short_desc: Ample sweetness across our recommended roasts, from unrefined sugars to dark caramels. Flavors range from black tea, cardamom, candied orange peel, licorice, and chocolate bar. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Kivu Kageyo
short_desc: Bittersweetness unfolds to flavors of unrefined sugar, creamy caramel, dashes of baking spice, chocolate-covered raisin, and a sharp hint of orange peel. Versatile in the roaster. City+ to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Ngororero
short_desc: Red honey and toasted sugar sweetness are accented by subtle notes of aromatic baking spices, like ginger and clove powder, with hints of orange, graham cracker, black tea, and dried cranberry. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Nyamasheke Gitwe
short_desc: Fragrant baking spice notes add a delicate touch to the light roasts of Gitwe, with transparent sweetness, black tea, dried apple, lemon brightness, and an aromatic Assam tea note in the aftertaste. City to Full City.

name: Rwanda Nyamasheke Mutovu
roast: City+ minimum to develop sweetness, but can be taken up to Full City+
short_desc: Cup sweetness shines through as Mutovu's strength. Pancake syrup, sorghum syrup, pungent burnt caramel, contrasting chocolate roast flavors, hints of raisin and wood spice aroma come through in the cup . City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Tanzania Sepukila Cooperative AB
short_desc: Lovely balance of acidity and sweetness that opens up to include flavors of turbinado and sucanat, dried date pieces, a cinnamon stick aromatic accent, hints of lemon juice, and a candied lemon peel bite. City to Full City.

name: Tanzania Tarime Town AA
short_desc: Syrupy sweetness and balanced bittersweet core flavors are accented by hints of coconut palm sugar, honey orange tea, grabby citrus, cocoa in the darker roasts, and a mouth cleansing, brisk brightness. City to Full City.

name: India Monsoon Malabar AA
roast: Full City+ to French - not a coffee for light roasting!
short_desc: Best in the darker roast levels and as a blend component, bringing body and bittering low tones to espresso. Earthy, pungent roast tones, hints of toasted grain and nut, barley, roasted corn, and more. Its strength is body, and will make an interesting cup for fans of earthy, low acid cup, and an excellent addition to an espresso blend (we use it in Liquid Amber!). Full City+ to French.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Aurelio Del Cerro
short_desc: A versatile coffee, delicious at a wide range of roasts. Brown sugar notes accented by drinking chocolate, raisin, toffee-nut, dark berry hint, and moderate acidity if roasted light. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Rosalio Villatoro
short_desc: Balanced cup flavors, turbinado, molasses, Brazil nut, and milder acidity that hints at red apple. Darker roasts show semi-sweet chocolate, and an understated berry note. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Virgilio
short_desc: Bittersweetness accented by notes of raw sugar, roasted nuts, hints of red berry. I've enjoyed a 1:1 melange of my City+/Full City roasts that melds berry-like acidity with rich chocolatey low tones. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Costa Rica Tarrazu Solis & Cordero
short_desc: There's a lot to uncover in this Costa Rican coffee, raspberry, honey mead, and an apple note that's on the winey side of ripeness. Ample sweetness makes the wilder fruit profiles seem fairly rounded. City+ to Full City+.

name: Costa Rica Tarrazu Cerro La Cruz
short_desc: Exceedingly sweet Costa Rican coffee that will serve you well as an everyday drinker. Notes of honey-glazed almond note, brisk black tea, torched sugar, red raisin, and Dutch hot chocolate. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: El Salvador Santa Ana Pacas
drying: Raised Bed Sun-Dried and Patio Sun-Dried
short_desc: All the tenets of a "daily drinking" coffee, caramel, almond confection, semi-sweet chocolate bar, and green apple hint. Pungent dark chocolate roast flavors when roasted dark. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Honduras San Vicente Comunidad Cabanas
short_desc: Brown sugar sweetness, walnut brownie, cocoa dusted almonds, Ghirardelli type dark chocolate and an herbal accent in the aftertaste adds contrast to the profile. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Nicaragua Acopio Suyatal
short_desc: The middle and dark roasts showcase impressive chocolate roast flavors, with notes of brown sugar and rice syrup, hazelnut, chocolate walnut brownie, and mild acidity. City to Full City+. Good for espresso and milk drinks.

name: Nicaragua Buenos Aires Maracaturra
short_desc: The bittersweetness is interspersed with subtle tea-like, bright cup characteristics. Molasses, burnt sugar candies, hints of Oolong tea, orange zest, and an incense-like aromatic note. City+ to Full City.

name: Nicaragua Finca Buenos Aires Lot 2
short_desc: Buenos Aires displays balanced sweetness and low tones, medium body, with notes of cooked sugars, chocolate-covered almond, and a long bittersweet finish. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Nicaragua Maracaturra Los Medios
short_desc: Los Medios has heftier sweetness and body than most of our other Maractaturras. Bittersweet base flavors are accented by hints of baked apple, cherimoya, and a tea-tannic aspect in the finish. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Panama Paso Ancho Carmen Estate
short_desc: Takes well to light and dark roasting. A nice tight range of flavors such as dark sugars, caramel, chocolate bittersweets, almond biscotti, and dark chocolate-covered macadamia nut. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Limu Boter Farm SWP Decaf
short_desc: Impressive sweetness for decaf, with bittersweet undertones, notes of barley malt syrup, date sugar, agave, dried fruit, chocolate bread, and hints of dried green herbs in the finish. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Peru Chanchamayo SWP Decaf
short_desc: A simple and succinct flavor profile that hints at brown sugar, cocoa powder, brown bread, cinnamon-sugar toast, and the aftertaste is has a pleasant chocolate malt note. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Nyamasheke SWP Decaf
short_desc: Bittering and sweet aspects of burned caramel, pungent cocoa roast flavors, molasses, dark spice note, aromatic hints of dried green herbs, like sage and marjoram. City+ to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Sweet Maria's Moka Java SWP Decaf Blend
processing: Dry Process and Wet Hulled, then Swiss Water Process Decaf
cultivar: Heirloom Cultivars, Abyssinia, Ateng, Tim Tim
short_desc: We refreshed the Moka Java ingredients! Still a cup backed with bittersweetness meshing with accent notes of cooked fruit and berry, burnt sugar, and earthy-sweet flavors mark the finish. City+ to Full City+. Great decaf espresso!

name: Timorindo SWP Decaf Blend
processing: Wet Hulled, Honey Process, and Wet Process, then Water Process Decaf
cultivar: Ateng, Jember, Tim Tim, Timor Hybrid
short_desc: This Timor/Indo blend makes a delicious non-caffeinated alternative, with bittersweet flavors, malted sweetness, cocoa crisped rice, and mild earth tones. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Java Sunda Ciwidey Gunung Nagara
short_desc: Caramelized sweetness in the foreground, with a hint of tannic yellow tea at City+. Layered bittersweetness at Full City, dark chocolate, torched marshmallow, and chocolate-covered raisin. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Java Sunda Tambak Ruyung
short_desc: The cup conjures images of brulee desserts, smoked sugar, an herbal stevia note, and cinnamon stick accent. Dark roasts develop a smoked chocolate note, and work so well as espresso. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Java Sunda Wet Hulled Pasir Ciparay
short_desc: Medium roasts put a spotlight on thick, bittersweet low tones, and complex herbal accents. It's like dark chocolate interspersed with hints of pine oil, clove, mint, and even a little rhubarb. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sulawesi Wet Hulled Benteng Alla
short_desc: Body and bittersweetness are two standout qualities, both impenetrably dense, and dark. Low-toned, mild acidity, inky dark cocoa, earthy cacao, hints of tarragon, marjoram, tobacco, and cedar. Full City to French.

name: Sumatra Aceh Simpang Teritit
short_desc: This is a deep, bass-note coffee, with low acidity, undertones of cocoa, oaky/earthy notes, hints of tobacco, barley, pepper cask, and peat. Medium and dark roasts highly recommended! Full City to French. Good for espresso.

name: Sumatra Anaerobic Kerinci Robusta
short_desc: Robusta is shockingly bitter, but this anaerobic lot has a mild sweetness wrapped within the intense unsweetened cocoa core, with hints of rustic fruit, leather, toasted grains, and dried herbs. Low toned, without acidity, and body is a perfect 10. City+ to French.

name: Sumatra Honey Process Kerinci Pendekar
short_desc: An herbal sweetness breaks through bittersweet low tones, with aromatic thyme atop notes of coconut palm sugar, barley malt, apple butter, and an orange oil note that brings bittering-bright contrast. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sumatra Lintong Sigumpar Village
cultivar: Lasuna, Onan Ganjang, Jember, Sigarar Utang
short_desc: This earth-toned Sumatra is a low acid cup with massive body, and pronounced bittersweetness. Notes of palm sugar, tobacco, shiso leaf, aromatic cedar, and dark cocoa. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sumatra Wet Process Kerinci Pendekar
short_desc: Foundation of burned sugar and toffee, with notes of pumpkin pie, sweetened condensed milk, basil, chocolate bittersweets, and acidic impression atypical of Sumatran coffee. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Timor Leste Dry Process Lekisala
short_desc: Fruited at a wide range of roasts, notes of dried banana and cooked berry, sweeteness has a hint of rustic palm sugar that lends an earth-toned flavor to the cup, and some aromatic cedar in the finish. City+ to Full City+.

name: Timor Leste Dukurai Daurfusu
short_desc: Crowd pleasing flavors of caramel and cocoa, hints of macadamia, dried herbs, flourless torte, roasted cacao nibs, and chocolate covered nut. Great dark roast option. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Timor Leste Nautuda
short_desc: Low-toned cup, with flavor that occupies the "Chocolatey" slice of the flavor wheel. Walnut brownie, dark chocolate-covered almond, rustic cocoa, and roasted peanut. City+ to French. Good for espresso.

name: Papua New Guinea Korgua AA
short_desc: Korgua brews a cup with complex sweetness of rustic sugars, and expands to include hints of plum tea, tamarind, dried apricot, and a nice acidic impression that is backed by an orange peel note. City to Full City.

name: Papua New Guinea Kuta Waghi
short_desc: This fresh arrival from Kuta Waghi shows simple syrup, honey, understated fruit notes like red raisin, and dried persimmon, along with tannic tea, and cocoa. Moderate acidity, without any sharpness. City to Full City.

name: Brazil Bahia Viviana Aparecida
short_desc: Outlier fruit flavors cause this Brazilian coffee to stand out. Green melon and plum notes have a winey ripeness behind them, as well as supportive sweetness, and flashes of acidity help keep rustic accents in check. City to Full City.

name: Brazil Dry Process Fazenda Furnas
short_desc: An incredibly bodied coffee with rustic notes of molasses and barley malt, hints of fruit and nuts, banana bread, dried peach, prune, and bittersweetness that never lets up. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso and blending.

name: Brazil Dry Process Irmas Pereira
short_desc: From light to dark, mild dried fruit notes add to a savory-sweet cup, with hints of molasses bread and hazelnut, as well as pungent roast flavors at the darker end of that spectrum. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Dry Process Pedra Branca
short_desc: Pedra Branca always tops our list of Brazilian coffees for dual use. Burnt sugars, robust bittersweetness, hints of cinnamon, cacao, and a subtle fruit note marks the aroma. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Pulp Natural Fazenda Sertao
short_desc: Approachable coffee, marked with bittersweet core flavors, body, and low level of acidity. Unrefined sugars, layered cocoa bittersweetness, almond milk, and sugar-glazed nuts. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Cajamarca Neftali Castro
short_desc: The cup sweetness is rooted in caramel and honey flavors at City roast level, shifting to sweetened dark chocolate bar at Full City. Top notes range from red honey, Turkish delights, and yellow apple. City to Full City+. Good for epresso.

name: Colombia Cresta El Hato
short_desc: Focused core sweetness in the cup, with notes of panela raw sugars, baking spice hints, red apple, and a nice malic acidic impression. Bittersweet possibilities when roasted dark. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Inza Antonia Oidor
short_desc: Aromatic sweetness and hints of fruit at a range of roast levels. Notes of sugar cane juice, apple tea, golden plum, and bergamot. Bittersweet with darker development, and hints of juicy grape, and dark berries. City to Full City.

name: Colombia Inza Vereda San Antonio
short_desc: Sweet all along the roast spectrum, with notes of brown sugars, dark honey, cinnamon-laced caramels, vanilla, dark chocolates, and fruited accents of apple, raisin, and candied orange. City to Full City+.

name: Colombia Inza Veredas Vecinas
short_desc: Impressive cup sweetness and body, molasses and brown sugar accents, pistachio torrone, pecan caramel, and tea-like tannic acidity. Dark roasts boost deep chocolate low tones perfect for brew or espresso. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Los Naranjos Heirloom Caturra
short_desc: Juicy and sweet, this heirloom lot conjures bright notes of mandarin and tangerine, a spritz of lemon, dark currant, raspberry herbal tea, and yellow cherry. Acidity falls somewhere between citric and malic. City to Full City.

name: Colombia Tolima Edward Sandoval Heirloom Bourbon
roast: City to City+ - light roasts highlight the aromatic cup characteristics
short_desc: A competition-level heirloom Bourbon ("Chiroso") in limited quantity. Aromatic sweetness,  refined fruits, and sparkling acidity, floral raw sugars, apple, Bartlett pear, white grape, cinnamon-apple tea. City to City+.*limited to 1# per customer

name: Peru El Diamante Roger Chilcon
region: El Diamante, San Jose de Lourdes
roast: City to Full City+ - very versatile coffee
short_desc: Focused sweetness of minimally-processed sugars both raw and caramelized, with accents of black currant, raisin, and spiced cider offering subtle contrast. Super versatile in the roaster. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Peru Organic Comite San Ignacio
cultivar: Catuai, Caturra, Pache, Catimor, Typica, Bourbon
short_desc: Balanced crowd-pleasing flavors, round body, a core of bittersweet chocolate, accented by molasses and torched sugars, and lower acidity that I appreciate in this context. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Peru Organic Cunyas Quispe
short_desc: A great option for darker roasts, where bittersweetness is in high volume. High % cacao bar, roasted nibs, hints of tamari almonds, sesame/chocolate marbled halva, and tobacco. Full City to French. Good for espresso.

name: Peru Organic Martin Tiberio Garcia
short_desc: Dense bittersweet notes of chocolate, and malted cocoa, with a nutty hints, and pleasantly mild acidity that works quite well with the simple cup profile. A super versatile coffee! City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Peru Pichanaki Alex Gomez
short_desc: Excels in medium-dark roasts, where chocolate flavors carry mild sweetness, Dutch cocoa, chocolate malted grain, cocoa puffed rice cereal, and chocolate-covered pistachio nut. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Peru Pitocuna Alejandro Huisa
short_desc: Cocoa-laden profile of Dutch cocoa, dark chocolate almond, and carob chips. Espresso shots are a home run too, with satiny mouthfeel, dark chocolate, candied orange peel, and walnut. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sweet Maria's Altiplano Blend
roast: Full City - Full City+ for deep chocolate roast flavors, and a subtle fruit hint
short_desc: This iteration includes a honey process ingredient that adds a touch of fruit to the intense chocolate roast flavors, along with flavors of high % cacao bar, rich chocolate truffles, syrupy dark grape and prune hints, and praline almond. Full City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sweet Maria's Decaf Espresso "Donkey" Blend
roast: As with all decafs, remember they roast faster and have the propensity to get away from you and end up darker than you expected. So attend to the roaster and stop the roast manually if possible to get it just right. Roast preference with espresso is up to you. I personally prefer the lighter N. Italian roast -just a bit more than a Full City.
short_desc: Fruited cup profile, some sweet bright accents, medium body. FC+ to a light Vienna is recommended.

name: Sweet Maria's Espresso Monkey Blend
roast: I like this blend best when the roast is stopped just as second crack becomes rapid, and shows no sign of slowing down. Actually, I like it a lot lighter than that too! I don't like this roasted to a dark, dark roast stage, Full French or Italian. This is because Brazilian coffees become ashy and began to bitter when roasted extremely dark. I believe strongly in a 36+ hour resting period before use for espresso extraction! It wont kill you to use it sooner... but you might notice sharp unpleasant notes.
short_desc: We blend this for body, balanced between high and low tones, fruited-chocolate roast flavors, and slightly rustic fruited accent notes. Our roast goal is in the beginning stages of 2nd crack ... we never "let it roll", so we recommend FC+ to light Vienna roast.

name: Sweet Maria's Ethiopiques Version 2.0
short_desc: At Full City, berry tones start to unfold and a persistent bittering cacao flavor is highlighted by notes of dehydrated blueberry and cranberry, as well as a dark citrus accent. Best with resting 48-72 hours. Full City to Full City+.

name: Sweet Maria's French Roast Blend
roast: I like this blend best roasted to the point where 2nd crack slows, but has not yet ended. Roast to the absolute end of 2nd crack, and you might as well be drinking roasted radish. I believe strongly in a 24 hour resting period for darker roasts.
short_desc: Designed to endure the rigors of dark roasting, and produce excellent pungent tastes, attractive bittersweet/carbony flavors, and great body.

name: Sweet Maria's Liquid Amber Espresso Blend
roast: I advocate a Northern Italian style roast (lighter espresso roast, really a French roast, stopped 30-45 seconds into 2nd crack), but the blend works very well at the darker Southern Italian style roast (a full French roast actually, at the peak of a rapid 2nd crack). Either way, get this into 2nd crack and allow proper resting that espresso demands: 48+ hours is best. This blend works great in air and drum roast machines and I developed it test-roasting on both. If you notice a tingly "baking soda effect" in your mouth, then the coffee could use more rest.
short_desc: A potent, pungent blend for espresso beverages. It's ideal for milk drinks, as this intense bittersweet cuts through the steamed milk. Caramel sweetness that turns pleasingly pungent with 2nd snaps, spice, cacao and semi-sweet chocolates, savory notes, long aftertaste. Monsooned coffee and a small percentage of Robusta add crema and body. Full City+ to French roast.

name: Sweet Maria's Moka Kadir Blend
short_desc: The all dry process Moka Kadir blend offers an underpinning of rich chocolate low tones, rustic palm sugar-type sweetness, earthy dried fruits, velvety mouthfeel, and finishing hints that are leathery, herbal, fruited, and of course bittersweet. Full City+ to Vienna. Good for espresso.

name: Sweet Maria's New Classic Espresso
roast: We recommend a range of roasts from FC, FC+ to light Vienna. That means just ending the roast just before 2nd crack (FC), a few snaps into 2nd crack (FC+), or as second crack begins to gain some momentum (Vienna)
short_desc: A classic, balanced espresso, but without the baggage of the old world espresso conventions ...and without robusta! The espresso has balanced bittersweet notes, thick and opaque body, almond and chocolate roast flavors, hints of spiced fruit in aroma. Full City+ and beyond.

name: Green Coffee Decaf Sample Set- 4 Pounds
short_desc: 4 pre-selected decaffeinated coffees from several different growing regions. An economical way for a beginner to start roasting or find some new favorites. We choose the coffees. Four 1lb bags of four different decaf coffees.*Please note that we can't make substitutions or take special requests for our samplers. Thank you!

name: Green Coffee Sample Set- Espresso
short_desc: The Espresso Sampler includes pre-selected Sweet Maria's Blends and single origin coffees that are good as espresso. Starting off with a sample set is an economical way to start roasting and become familiar with origin flavor characteristics. Some of the single origin coffees and blends will not be available to order from our main coffee list since they are coffees that are going out of stock or are for sample sets only. You will receive 4 or 8 different 1 lb bags of green coffee.

name: Green Coffee Sample Set- Regular
short_desc: Pre-selected coffees from some of the different growing regions we offer. Starting off with a sample set is an economical way to start roasting and become familiar with origin flavor characteristics. These coffees will not typically be available to order from the our main coffee list since they are coffees that are going out of stock or are for sample sets only. You will receive either 4 or 8 different 1 lb bags of green coffee..

name: Green Coffee Subscription
short_desc: Auto-shipped, pre-selected coffees from some of the different growing regions we offer. These coffees will not typically be available to order from the our main coffee list since they are coffees that are going out of stock or are for sample sets only. No special requests are accepted. You will receive either 4 or 8 different 1 lb bags of green coffee shipped once a month or every 2 months, your choice! Shipping is not included in the price. Orders will ship via the shipping method chosen at checkout.

name: Next Roast 5/30: El Salvador Santa Ana Pacas
drying: Raised Bed Sun-Dried and Patio Sun-Dried
short_desc: Roasted to City: Caramel, almond confection and  semi-sweet chocolate bar.Our next roast day is 6/13. Pre-order a bag of this limited coffee feature while supplies last!

name: Next Roast 5/30: Rwanda Ngororero
short_desc: Roasted to City+ : Graham cracker, Black tea, and Dried cranberry.Our next roast day is 6/13. Pre-order a bag of this limited coffee feature while supplies last!

name: ROASTED COFFEE Brazil Dry Process Irmas Pereira
short_desc: Roasted to City+: Mild dried fruit notes, with hints of molasses bread and hazelnut.Our next roast day is 5/30. Order a bag of this limited coffee feature while supplies last!

name: ROASTED COFFEE Burundi Kabarore Commune Yandaro
short_desc: Roasted to City+ : Mild yellow tea, Zesty orange and Lemon accentsOur next roast day is 5/30. Order a bag of this limited coffee feature while supplies last!

name: Roasted Coffee Subscription
short_desc: Enjoy 2 lbs of freshly roasted coffee from our Probat roaster at Sweet Maria's Coffee. With a roasted coffee subscription we ship you two different single origin coffees roasted between a City-Full City roast, packaged in resealable valve bags.

name: ROASTED COFFEE: Tanzania Mbamba Namku Peaberry
short_desc: Roasted to Full City : Rustic sweetness, Baking chocolate and Sorghum syrup.Our next roast day is 5/16. Order a bag of this limited coffee feature while supplies last!

name: ROASTED ESPRESSO Liquid Amber Blend 5/16
short_desc: Roasted on 5/16/2023 to Light ViennaRustic sweetness, spices and savory notes.

name: ROASTED ESPRESSO Liquid Amber Blend 5/2
short_desc: Roasted on 5/2/2023 to Light ViennaRustic sweetness, spices and savory notes.

name: ROASTED ESPRESSO Monkey Blend 5/16
short_desc: Roasted on 5/16/2023 to Full City ++Bittersweet chocolate, licorice and dark fruit.

name: ROASTED ESPRESSO New Classic Espresso Blend
short_desc: Roasted on 5/2/2023 to Full CityChocolate roast notes, almond and spiced fruit.

name: 'SALE - Hello: Ethiopia & Kenya Coffee Set
processing: Wet Process (Washed), and 1 Dry Process (Natural) Ethiopia
roast: All coffees in this set benefit from light roasting. Please see the enclosed card for our roasting notes and a pictorial representation of the roasts we used for these specific cupping notes and scores.
short_desc: A selection of SIX one pound bags of our highest-rated green coffees that explores the fantastic range of flavors found within Ethiopia and Kenya. This attractively packaged set includes cupping notes based on specific roasts, with images of those roasts and color charts that help take the guesswork out of matching our roast levels. A discounted price for these coveted coffees only sweetens the deal! This edition is 500 sets, with a limit of 2 per customer.*see description for the list of coffees

name: Burundi Dry Process Agahore
short_desc: Delicious dry process flavors like fruit jams, blackberry reduction, red raisin, natural dried apricot, along with a nice layer of rustic bittersweet cocoa, immense body, and hints of blueberry and clove spice in the nose. City+ to Full City+.

name: Burundi Dry Process Kibingo Station
short_desc: Intense fruit and biscuity sweetness bring to mind raspberry pie, buckwheat pancakes with blueberry syrup, barley malt syrup, yellow cherry, freeze dried strawberry, apricot filling, with a slight berry-like acidic impression. City to Full City.

name: Burundi Gatara Masha
short_desc: So sweet at a wide range of roasts, honey, sugar in the raw, honeysuckle, spiced flecks of cinnamon and all spice, essence of dried papaya, cascara fruit tea, lemony vibrance, and chocolatey dark roasts. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Burundi Gaterama Agahore Station
short_desc: Agahore is aromatic and sweet, maple syrup, sugar in the raw, whole clove, peach skin accent, aromatic bitters syrup, a hint of floral rooibos tea, and moderate lemon acidity in all our roasts. City to Full City.

name: Burundi Kabarore Commune Yandaro
short_desc: A stunning coffee, honey and raw sugar sweetness, hints of cantaloupe, mild yellow tea, fresh peach and apricot, and elegant acidity connects the sweetness to a brisk tea-like finish. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Burundi Kayanza Gahahe
short_desc: Light roasts are complex, floral and bright, augmented by spice and fresh fruit notes. Honey and sugar cane soda, fruited flavors of apricot jam, floral nectarine, with a sweet/spiced aftertaste. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Burundi Yeast Fermentation Yandaro
short_desc: Pronounced tea notes and baking spice aroma, Earl Grey, Good Earth and green tea, cinnamon gum, cardamom, a lively lemon note, while darker roasts unlock cinnamon-spiced chocolate and a dark fruit hint. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Cameroon Caplami Java Cultivar
short_desc: An interesting, thick bodied cup from a lesser seen coffee origin (at least on our list). Notes of caramel, molasses, rustic chocolate, pipe tobacco, malted grains, cinnamon stick, and earthy sandalwood. Full City to Full City+.

name: Congo Organic Dry Process Kabare Katana
short_desc: The cup brings together rustic fruits and bittersweetness, with notes of stewed stone fruit, dried cherry, rustic natural wines, pipe tobacco, and earthy dark chocolate tempering things. City to Full City+.

name: Congo Organic Kirumba Kavisa
short_desc: Excellent sweetness, with a lively citrus side that places it in line with many of our Kenyan coffees. Sweet fruity notes of grape and currant, tart orange acidity, and earthy Matcha tea note underscores a tannic finish. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Agaro Kedamai
short_desc: Kedamai makes a syrupy sweet coffee with hefty stone fruit flavors like juicy apricot nectar, and peach preserves, aromatic mulling spices, delicate orange blossom, and a peach tea note. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Agaro Kedamai Coop
short_desc: Syrupy sweet coffee with fruited intensity too, flavors of stone fruit nectars, peach tea, and dried Turkish apricot, along with mulling spice and orange glaze aromatics, and clean fruited acidity. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Aba Mecha
short_desc: Lighter roasts show brighter fruit characteristics, while darker pulls out chocolate bittersweets. Notes of strawberry, apricot, fruit tea, cinnamon apple sauce, and rustic sweetness shadowing the cup. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Benti Nenka
short_desc: Fruits find solid footing alongside floral highlights, notes of strawberry, raspberry preserves, stone fruit juice, cherry candy, watermelon, fermented berry, fruit compote, star jasmine, and a whole lot more. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Benti Nenka
short_desc: This fruited cup profile is sure to turn some heads. Notes of raspberry, blueberry, rustic dried fig and apricot, with fragrant notes of rue herb and floral berry adding to a complex retronasal aspect. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Buno Dambi Uddo
short_desc: Aromatic fruits like plum, blueberry, blackberry, Galia melon, and passion fruit florals, with moderate acidity that's like stone fruit. Add an overlay of deep chocolate bass notes with deeper roasting. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Guji Gerba
short_desc: A powerhouse in the fruit flavor department, Gerba promises a bouquet of berry and other fruit-floral highlights, notes of ripe strawberry, cherry, blueberry, cocoa accents, and such a complex cup aroma. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Hambela Buliye
short_desc: Delicious plump fruit flavors, blueberry preserves, peach, dark plum, with notes of sorghum syrup, dried date, and a floral berry aroma. Chocolate-drizzled fruits with darker roast development. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Yirga Cheffe Mengesha Farm
short_desc: Mengesha Farm pushes the "wow" factor with this one. Floral blueberry, blackberry kiefer, berry hard candies, chocolate-dipped banana, hints of jasmine and ripe strawberry, with orange acidic impression that helps tie it all together. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Gedeb Banko Gotiti
short_desc: Rose and jasmine flower aromatics in full bloom, with refined sweetness, pristine acidity, and aromatic flavors of honey, pink bubblegum, nectarine and sweet citrus. Makes a fantastic pour over brew! City to City+.

name: Ethiopia Gera Ayetu Farm
short_desc: Juicy fruit accents, and delicate aromatics ride high above a moderately sweet brew. Raw brown sugars, dried peach, apricot, bergamot citrus and orange blossom florals. Full City makes impressive espresso too. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Guji Hambela Dabaye
short_desc: Can we talk about how incredibly floral this coffee is? Like Gesha, or a super floral Yirga Cheffe. Star jasmine, aromatic raw honey, white grape juice, lychee, soft citrus accents, and pink bubblegum. Incredible pour over! City to City+.

name: Ethiopia Guji Shakiso Reji
short_desc: Light roasts have a nice bright side, complex base sweetness of raw sugar cane, accented by caramel, a lemon meringue pie note, subtle hints of peach tea, herbal rue, and faint florals. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Nensebo Refisa
short_desc: Aromatic and sweet, with bracing lemon-like acidity when roasted light. Hints of yuzu citrus and lemon, pink fruit gum, honeydew melon, fragrant jasmine florals and bergamot tea. Incredible depth of flavor! City to City+.

name: Ethiopia Organic Agaro Duromina
short_desc: Always such a bodied cup, Duromina's flavors convey amber honey sweetness, tangy citrus at the sides of your tongue, red apple, orange marmalade, peach, stone fruit skins, and a complex rue herbal hint. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Organic Gera Genji Challa
short_desc: Underlying white honey sweetness, aspects of fresh mango and peach add a juicy quality to the cup, with sweet and tangy citrus notes, and complex aromatic highlights of fresh rue and jasmine up top. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Organic Gera Nano Challa
short_desc: White honey sweetness opens up to fruited notes of fresh nectarine, apricot, peach, lively orange, golden raisin, and acidity that is permeated by citrus-y hints, as well as aromatics of tenadam and lemongrass. City to Full City. Good for espresso too!

name: Ethiopia Uraga Raro Boda
short_desc: What a special pour over brew this makes, potent floral aromatics, perfumed jasmine pearls, ripe fruit-type florals, sweetness of simple syrup and light honey, bubble gum, peach and mango hard candy accents. City- to City+.

name: Ethiopia Yirga Cheffe Chelbesa Danche
short_desc: A standout Yirga Cheffe! Clean, floral, and bright, with pristine sweetness that's marked by juicy notes of citrus and peach fruits, and complex aroma of jasmine, freesia, fresh rue and coriander. City to City+.

name: Ethiopia Yirga Cheffe Chelchele
short_desc: Chelchele has sweetness akin to corn syrup and molasses that keeps the cup feeling substantial amidst a delicate floral top note, hints of peach, nectarine, star fruit, and some woody aromatic incense in the finish. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Yukiro Cooperative
short_desc: Super clean, bright cup, sure to be the star of the show in any setting, sweetness of honey, fresh apricot, peachy florals, jamaica tea, orange juice, lime aroma, and citrus acidic impressions provide a sturdy backbone. City to City+.

name: Kenya Kiambu Fram Farm AA
short_desc: Sweet citrus notes like mandarin, Navel orange, juicy pink grapefruit help highlight acidity without feeling grabby. Hints of stone fruit, spiced juniper berry, as well as a cherry accent in the aftertaste. Amazing cup clarity. City to City+.

name: Kenya Kiambu Fram Farm AB
short_desc: Intense cup sweetness, with fruited characteristics like mandarin orange and other citrus notes, dark berry, black currant tea, snappy acidity, and an intoxicating fruit-floral aroma in light roasts. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Kiambu Fram Farm Peaberry
short_desc: Fruited cup flavors are backed by juicy sweetness, with flavor profiles of grape, red berries, a twist of lemon that elevates acidity, and aromatic elements that hint at jamaica and raspberry iced teas. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Kiambu Ndumberi Peaberry
short_desc: Fruited top notes push forward in the cooling cup, with juicy body, complex aromatics, and bright cup characteristics. Orange, raspberry, green apple, grape jelly, cinnamon tea, five spice, floral rose hips, and tea-tannic finish. City to City+.

name: Kenya Kiambu Ngaita Peaberry
short_desc: The cup aroma is imbued with delicate tea notes, Earl Grey and bergamot citrus, cardamom tea, and lemongrass, along with a clean sweetness that weaves together fruit hints of ripe mango, apricot, and a fresh strawberry. City to City+.

name: Kenya Kiambu Riabai AB
short_desc: Spiced aromatics and impressive sweetness lead to a brew profile saturated with cane sugar, lemonade, orange, and a flurry of herbal tea notes such as cinnamon-apple, and tart black currant tea. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Kirinyaga Kainamui Peaberry
short_desc: Kainamui is amazing start to finish! Juicy fruit flavors accented by aromatic spices, mulled grape juice, cranberry, spiced holiday punch, gooseberry, acidity that twists at your tongue, but is tamed by the strong sweetness. City to City+.

name: Kenya Kirinyaga Kamwangi AB
short_desc: Citrus flavors resonate in the cup, bright acidity supported by notes of orange spritzer, lemonade, orange tea, pomegranate, candied citrus peel, juicy boysenberry and blackberry. Excellent cup clarity in pour over brews! City to Full City.

name: Kenya Kirinyaga Kamwangi Peaberry
short_desc: Deliciously fruited, with accents of Naval orange, lemon custard, orange marmalade, tart fresh squeezed lemon, and a dusting of all-spice and cardamom. Light and bright, though juicier body in medium roasts. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Kirinyaga Kamwangi Peaberry
short_desc: Deliciously fruited, with accents of Naval orange, cranberry, orange marmalade, plump grape, fresh squeezed lemon, and a dusting of all-spice and cardamom. Light and bright, though juicier body in medium roasts. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Kirinyaga Thunguri Peaberry
short_desc: Thunguri will satisfy those looking for a 'light and bright' Kenya, with notes of lemonade, blackberry, orange, mixed berry jam, fragrant Darjeeling tea, candy coated cardamom seeds, cranberry, and an aromatic whiff of rose potpourri. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Kirinyaga Wanja AA
short_desc: Exemplary Kenyan cup flavors, juicy tangerine, grabby grapefruit, aromatic lemongrass tea, along with hints of red berry, sparkling citrus acidity, and resonant baking spice notes in the long finish. Fantastic pour over! City to City+.

name: Kenya Muranga Kagumoini AB
short_desc: The cup is vibrant with ripe mandarin orange acidity, floral honey and raw sugars, fruited notes of dried peach, pink grapefruit, orange juice, grape jelly (in darker roasts), and perfumed hints of baking spices in the finish. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Muranga Nguku AB
short_desc: Forward facing sweetness of demerara, sucanat, and simple syrup, with notes of rooibos tea, huckleberry, and refreshing Meyer lemon vibrance, all sums up to a complex cup that's Kenyan coffee all the way! City to City+.

name: Kenya Muranga Nguku Peaberry
short_desc: Fruit flavors are light and elegant, with notes of red berry, citrus, and an attractive aromatic profile of Darjeeling tea, clove, bergamot oil, and a hint of herbal bitters. A fantastic coffee for pour over brewing. City to City+.

name: Kenya Muranga Riakiberu Peaberry
short_desc: Restrained fruit flavors of black currant, raisin, tamarind, berry, and lemon radler marry with sweetness of simple syrup to caramel depending on roast level, and with moderately bright acidity, and such a sweet finish. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Gaikundo AA
short_desc: Mouth refreshing acidity lies at the heart of Gaikundo's cup, a high toned coffee of vivid brightness with punchy profiles of blood orange, raspberry lemonade, and baking spice hints marking aroma. City to City+.

name: Kenya Nyeri Gathaithi AA
roast: City to Full City; acidity goes from citric in lighter roasts to berry-like closer to Full City
short_desc: Bright acidity helps organize the array of flavors like red grape, cranberry jelly, black currant, tart rhubarb, pear juice, aromatic baking spices, and red plum. An easy favorite, with so much to reveal with different levels of roast. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Gatomboya Peaberry
short_desc: Gatomboya's sweet cup profile is built around a multiplicity of fruited flavors and top note highlights, such as grape, peach tea, plum jam with a tangy hint of orange peel, and vibrant stone fruit acidity. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Gatugi AB
short_desc: Fruited accents are woven into intense cup sweetness. Hints of honey tangerine and orange, red berry medley, fruited acidity, and baking spice aromatics. Light roasts is where Gatugi really struts its stuff! City to City+.

name: Kenya Nyeri Gichichi AA
short_desc: Delicate aromatics and sweetness make for an elegant Kenyan cup. Light roasts yield flavors of sugar cane juice, ginger chews, Earl Grey tea, berry, herbal bitters aroma, and a lemony bright spot too. City to City+.

name: Kenya Nyeri Ichamama AA
short_desc: It's the sweet/citrus combo that rings out loud and clear in this AA Ichamama coffee. Demerara sugar and brisk lemon top the list, with hints of raspberry, orange, ginger powder, chamomile, and lemongrass teas. City to City+.

name: Kenya Nyeri Kagumo AA
short_desc: Light roasts highlight stone fruits, black tea with lemon, tongue-twisting acidity, and a sweetness of cream soda and brown sugar. Full City roasts show a surprising berry note amidst balanced bittersweetness. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Kagumo AB
short_desc: Kagumo is a bright, juicy coffee, with compact sweetness of raw sugars, notes of pomegranate, blackberry tea, honeydew melon, orange drink (like Tang), and complex spices make for an aromatic aftertaste. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Kagumo Peaberry
roast: City to City+ for the most dynamic, bright cups
short_desc: A stunning cup profile of juicy sweet fruits, and remarkable aromatic depth. Notes of red fruit punch, pineapple, orange tea, melon fruit salad, spiced cranberry juice, and fruited brightness that's not too grabby. City to City+.

name: Kenya Nyeri Maganjo AA
short_desc: Top notes are wrapped in a blanket of raw sugars, with accents of red berry, lemon gelatin, holiday ginger spice cookies, and a dark black tea/tannic bittering quality in the aftertaste. Tame acidity for Kenya. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Mahiga AA
short_desc: Fruit flavors find substantial sweetness in the middle roasts, tangy pomello and tangerine, stone fruits, and aromatic cardamom and mace. Deeper roasts show grape, blackberry, and chocolatey low tones. City+ to Full City+.

name: Kenya Nyeri Mahiga Peaberry
short_desc: Mahiga makes a refined Kenya cup, with tea-like tangy notes of jamaica flower and citrus teas, blueberry, a lemongrass citrus accent, apricot, and a maple sugar sweetness adds an aromatic flair. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Thika Karatu Peaberry
short_desc: Complex citrus flavors feed into a bright cup, ripe blood orange, tangy kumquat, citrus zest, Meyer lemon, along with rose tea florals, mulled apple juice, a brisk note of raspberry iced tea. City to City+.

name: Kenya Thika Oreti AA
short_desc: This AA lot from Oreti farm is a potent cup from start to finish. Citrus notes come through loud and clear, with ruby red grapefruit, orange jelly, hints fruit punch, ripe peach and complex baking spice aromatics. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Thika Oreti AB
short_desc: Lively cup characteristics shine bright when roasted light, brisk flavors of black iced tea with lemon, pink lemonade and orange. Aromatic spiced notes cap things off, along with a tea-tannic mouthfeel in the long finish. City to City+.

name: Kenya Thika Oreti Peaberry
short_desc: Incredible light roast pour-over, vibrant and tart cup, with flavors of orange, lemonade, and grabby grapefruit, opening up to hints of cranberry juice, pomegranate, lemon, boysenberry, rose hip tea, and a whole lot more! City roast level preferred.

name: Rwanda Dry Process Kanyege
short_desc: Juicy blackberry and fresh fig notes tucked behind substantial chocolate roast taste, with hints of dried blueberry, date, caramelized sugar, truffle, and fruited acidity. Punctuated bittersweetness when roasted dark. City to Full City.

name: Rwanda Dry Process Macuba
short_desc: Berry notes leave a near floral impression, like ripe blackberry, blueberry, along with fruited acidity, and darker roasts tie in a delicious bittersweet undertone, like strawberries dipped in chocolate sauce. City to Full City+.

name: Rwanda Dry Process Nyamiyaga
short_desc: There's a nice, juicy profile to be found, City roast bring out fruit salad with raspberry, zesty orange, and a tropical hint, whereas darker roast yield plump blueberry with rustic bittersweets. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Honey Process Gatare
short_desc: I find the cup flavors to be so well balanced, caramely sweet, acidity that's integrated into cup sweetness, hints of Chai spice, tea, glazed orange peel, and moderate bittersweetness in medium roasts. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Honey Process Kanyege
short_desc: Caramel, butter toffee, honey graham cracker, restrained notes of black tea, candied orange peel, and ample acidity. Easy honey to roast, with decadent chocolate when roasted dark. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Honey Process Karambi
short_desc: Clean honeyed sweetness and silky mouthfeel give way to accent notes of honey comb, raspberry, fresh fig, Assam tea, chocolate buttercream, cocoa butter, and vanilla cream soda. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Karongi Gitesi
short_desc: Impressive base sweetness marked by Darjeeling spiced tea, black currant, and a hint of lemon adds to the overall acidic impression. Elegant pour over, and spiced chocolate as espresso. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Ngororero
short_desc: Cup flavors have a delicious aromatic spice quality of whole clove, candied ginger, and cinnamon stick, with crisp red fruit and elderberry teas that convey a floral aspect, and delicate acidic impression. City to Full City.

name: Rwanda Nyamasheke Macuba
short_desc: A sturdy-sweet cup, crisped toffee crust, fragrant honey, dulce de leche, with acidic aspects of brisk tea, and a juicy note of cherry and raspberry. Layered chocolate flavors at Full City, with a dark berry hue. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Nyamasheke Nyakabingo
short_desc: Baking spice notes are the star of the show standing out against balanced sweetness, clove, Darjeeling tea, cardamom, hibiscus tea, dried cherry, orange rind, floral hint, and brisk lemon-like acidity. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Rubavu Rwinyoni
short_desc: Rwinyoni yields mouth pleasing acidity and with complex sweetness of caramel, butterscotch chips, nougat, white chocolate, accents of lemon tea, cinnamon toast, and red raisin. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Rulindo Tumba
region: Tumba Town, Rulindo District, Northern Province
short_desc: Abundant sweetness accented by hints of pomegranate, berry tea, dried tamarind, and a brisk note of black tea with lemon. Bittersweet chocolate with a note of Dr. Pepper when roasted dark. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Rusizi Gaseke
short_desc: A sweet backdrop of complex sugars like raw sugar cane juice, muscovado, aromatic brulee sugar, with restrained top notes of Earl Grey tea, a hint of masala Chai, and dried strawberry note. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Tanzania Mara Tarime Peaberry
short_desc: A backdrop of palm sugar-like sweetness is accented by notes of dried date, rustic fig, and tamarind, with a woody incense aroma. Immense bittersweetness and syrupy body when roasted dark. City+ to Full City+.

name: Tanzania Mbamba Namku AA
short_desc: An underlying flavor of burnt sugars is accented by orange spice and cinnamon stick hints, candied citrus peel flavor that informs acidic impression, and wraps up with raspberry black tea in the finish. City to Full City.

name: Tanzania Mbamba Namku Peaberry
roast: Full City to Full City+ - a great coffee for dark roasted espresso!
short_desc: Dark roasts pull out brooding low tones, rustic sweetness, baking chocolate, sorghum syrup, dark agave, and tobacco. Lightly fruited too. Fantastic for milk drinks or a daily dark roast brew. Full City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Tanzania Mbinga Peaberry
short_desc: The cup sweetness is resilient to roast, notes of caramel, creme brulee, and toasted sesame cookie. Light roasts have a hint of orange, and rustic aromatic note of Cavendish tobacco. City+ to Full City+.

name: Yemen Al Qafr Hawari
short_desc: Follows a rustic sweet blueprint, with notes of pistachio cookie, malted chocolate, ginger powder, sesame candies, corn syrup, and tobacco leaf. Super chocolatey dark roasts that stand up to milk! City+ to Vienna. Good for espresso.*We're donating ten cents of every pound to Doctors Without Borders who help provide much needed humanitarian relief in the region.

name: Yemen Bani Haraz
short_desc: Middle roasts build out a bittersweet chocolate core, expanding to creamy Brazil nut and raw cacao, notes of dried fig, pepitas, chocolate malted grains, brown ale, cooked pumpkin, earthy rhubarb, cola, and some palo santo incense. City+ to French. Good for espresso.*We're donating ten cents of every pound to Doctors Without Borders who help provide much needed humanitarian relief in the region.

name: Yemen Khulani Amer
short_desc: Flavors range from sweet to savory, with fruited complexity wrapped into the earthy cup. Rustic bittersweetness, dried apple, goji berry, banana protein shake, Ovaltine, dark cocoa, sesame snacks, leather, za'atar, and Monukka honey. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Yemen Mokha Hajjah
region: Bani Awam and Mabyan Districts, Hajjah Governorate
short_desc: Shadowy low tones in medium and dark roasts are anything but delicate! Big cocoa flavors, roast intensity, and notes of baking chocolate, cacao, and barley malt syrup are woven into the creamy texture. Full City to French. Excellent espresso!

name: Yemen Mokha Matari
short_desc: Matari is always a standout Yemeni coffee, this year's showing balanced chocolate flavors, fruited sweetness, chai spice, dried apricot, banana, berry, baked apple, sandalwood, aromatic pipe tobacco...as complex as they come! City+ to Vienna. Good for espresso.*We're donating ten cents of every pound to Doctors Without Borders who help provide much needed humanitarian relief in the region.

name: Zambia Dry Process Kateshi Estate
short_desc: Thick body, fruited chocolate, and surprising cup clarity for a dry process coffee. An apple note verges on winey, along dried pear, and an interesting arbol chili hint that reads like spiced mole chocolate. City+ to Full City+.

name: Zambia Mafinga Peaberry
short_desc: Chewy bittersweetness you can almost sink your teeth into, molasses, cocoa powder, Tootsie Roll chocolate taffy, subtle hints of fruit and fresh herbs, with moderate acidity level. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Zambia Yeast Fermentation Mafinga
short_desc: Yeast fermentation seems to have made quite an impact on flavors, a wild cup of fermented fruit, plum wine, apple cider vinegar, star fruit, aromatic cedar and pine wood, and moderate acidity in the lighter roasts. City+ to Full City+.

name: Espresso Workshop #49 Balayage
processing: Wet Process, and Dry Process coffees
roast: Full City to Full City+ - I don't recommend a rolling 2nd Crack
short_desc: Fruited flavors tempered by bittersweetness, Ghirardelli dark chocolate chips, ganache filling, chocolate banana pudding, cherry cordials, dried blueberry aroma, orange hint, and smokey cacao finish. Full City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Espresso Workshop #50 - The Skullet
processing: Wet Process, and Dry Process coffees
roast: Full City to Full City+ - I don't recommend a rolling 2nd Crack
short_desc: Layered bittersweet flavors are accented by fruited hints, and creamy mouthfeel ensures a very long finish! Chocolate-forward profile of high % cacao bar and baking chocolate adds a sharpness to the cup, with hints of stewed plum, and chocolate-covered dried fruits. Full City to Full City+. Fantastic espresso!

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Aler Villatoro
short_desc: Cup sweetness shows a level of intensity that hangs around in the aftertaste, mild mannered hints of apple, raisin, and  pleasant acidity. Full City boasts bean-to-bar chocolate and big body. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Bojonalito
short_desc: Balanced core bittersweetness has impressive chocolate undercurrent, with notes of vanilla, brown sugar, dark toffee, almond, high % cacao bar, and salted caramel. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Boqueroncito
short_desc: Ticks off the boxes of a perfect daily drinker: moderately sweet, bodied, hefty cocoa tones, mild top notes that add interest. Cinnamon-spiced cocoa, raisin, chocolate biscotti. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul El Paraiso
short_desc: A sweet undercurrent lays the groundwork for a balanced daily drinking coffee, with crisp acidity in light roasts that structures cup flavors. Notes of light brown sugar, caramel, dried apple, semi-sweet chocolate. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Flavio Del Cerro
short_desc: Brews incredibly well at a wide roast range, mouthwatering sweetness of unrefined sugar and fruited accents, bittersweet intensity, tart apple, cocoa nibs, berry finishing note, and bracing malic acidity. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Idmar Velasquez
short_desc: Balanced flavors of unrefined sugar, cocoa, and creamy nut wrapped up in a full bodied brew. Tops my list of SO espresso, buttery mouthfeel, dark chocolate truffle, orange peel hint. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Jose Villatoro
short_desc: Well rounded cup profile, raw sugars, fruited acidity, hints of dried cranberry and apple, cocoa dusted walnut. Darker roasts show inky body and bittersweetness with a hint of berry. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Michicoy
short_desc: This wonderful dual-use coffee has a nice culmination of raw sugars and cocoa, with a fruited hint in the middle roast range. Dutch drinking cocoa, almond, apple, and mild acidity. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Pena Blanca
short_desc: Juicy mouthfeel helps tease out a hint of Gala apple, while balanced bittersweetness takes the form of dark cacao bar with a ribbon of caramel. Pear acidity in the lighter roasts, big body at all roast levels. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul San Pedro Necta
short_desc: A thick bodied coffee with compact bittersweetness, and a subtle top note of dried green apple that informs acidity. Full City roasts boast high % dark chocolate bar laced with caramelized sugars. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Honduras Comayagua Donato Java
short_desc: City+ ensures a well developed sweetness, and balanced cup flavors, with complex herbal accents of ricola, bell pepper, and the woody tang of steeped lemon grass. City+ to Full City.

name: Honduras Ocotepeque San Marcos
short_desc: Bittersweet low tones are offset by convincing caramelized sweetness, and cools to top notes of rice pudding, toasted pumpkin seeds, sunflower butter, and tarragon chocolate truffles. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Honduras Productores de La Paz
short_desc: Versatile in the roaster, with unrefined sugars, the creamy sweetness of raw cashew and macadamia nuts, chocolate almond milk, and Cadbury-type milk chocolate. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Costa Rica Chirripo Finca Jose
roast: City to Full City+; excels at a wide range of roast
short_desc: Core flavor elements are molasses-type sugars and bittersweet roast tones, as well as raw and roasted nut notes (pistachio comes to mind), and bracing tea brightness. Top notes of apple tea, cinnamon stick, and dried berry. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Costa Rica Don Oscar Hermanos Solis
short_desc: Restrained complexity, brown sugar, hazelnut, roasted barley, apple-like acidity, and a clean, disappearing aftertaste. Chocolate at the front of the cup in darker roasts. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Costa Rica Helsar Eliomar Lopez
roast: City to Full City+ - very versatile coffee
short_desc: Clean sweetness ala sugar-in-the-raw, malted beer grains, subtle hop aroma, and a soft but elegant citric acidity. Eliomar's coffee is a good candidate for dark roasts too (see review). City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Costa Rica Honey Corazon de Jesus
short_desc: The cocoa/raw sugar base flavor cools notes of dark berries, yellow cherry, and baked apple. Chocolate roast tones abound in darker roasts, while City roasts are refreshingly bright. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Costa Rica Honey Palmichal Vecindario
short_desc: Stellar single origin espresso, and chocolatey, balanced brew in the middle roasts. Barley malt syrup,  molasses, chocolate milk, hazelnut chocolate, and chocolate mochi. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Costa Rica Honey Process Familia Urena
short_desc: Silky body helps convey the depth of sweetness, and chocolatey low tones in the darker roast. Burnt sugar, almond, raisin hint, high % cacao chocolate, dried coconut and anise. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Costa Rica Jardin de Aromas
short_desc: Solid muscovado sweetness, bittersweet Dutch cocoa, tangy coconut water and dried coconut chips, and subtle spiced herbal teas mark the aroma in light roasts. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Costa Rica Red Honey Los Santos
short_desc: Persistent sweetness through to the finish, brown sugar, sweet baked pastries, an apple note that hints at malic acidity. Full City roasts give weight to the chocolate low tones. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Costa Rica Tarrazu Cafetales de Dota
short_desc: Crowd pleasing, middle roasts trade brightness for body, with cocoa roast flavors, chocolate biscuit, bittering cacao, light fruited hint, caramelized sugar, and raw pistachio nut. City+ to French. Good for espresso.

name: Costa Rica Tarrazu La Casona
short_desc: Balanced sweetness in the cup, with hints of molasses, bittersweet cocoa, roasted barley, apple-like acidic impression, and nuanced finishing flavors that come to a point. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Costa Rica Yellow Honey La Guaria
short_desc: Rounded sweetness with bittersweet cocoa underneath, hints of raisin and date, and peachy acidity. Dark roasts make tremendous single origin espresso, chocolate cherry truffle, with tangy glazed orange peel. City to Full City+.

name: Costa Rica Zarcero Finca Salaca
short_desc: Finca Salaca is a balanced coffee with just enough nuance to make it interesting. Molasses, burnt sugar, bittersweet chocolate from middle to finish, hints of caramel apple and berry as it cools. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: El Salvador Apaneca Finca Miravalles
short_desc: A convergence of cocoa roast flavors and brown sugar that holds up to dark roasting, layers of dark chocolate, creamy nut tones, and inky body. Great coffee for milk drinks too! City+ to Full City+. Good espresso.

name: El Salvador Comasagua San Antonio
short_desc: Molasses, date sugar, bittersweet chocolate, toffee almond, and sesame hint. Darker roasts really bring out low tones and incredibly thick body. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: El Salvador Dry Process Finca San Luis
short_desc: Intense cup flavors are hard to miss, rustic cup character, pungent burnt sugars, fruited notes of ripe pear, plum and blackberry wines, coconut water, canned pineapple, and a bittersweet finish. City to Full City.

name: El Salvador Finca La Esperanza
short_desc: Balanced cup flavors are sure to win favor, interplay of raw sugar and almond, creamy body and loaded with chocolate roast flavors. Acidity is mild, but tea-like, with a dried apple note adding to the effect. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: El Salvador Finca Miravalle Tabi
short_desc: Raw sugar sweetness counteracts ample roast tones, notes of Dutch cocoa, Brazil nut, chocolate-covered raisin, flourless torte, moderate acidity level. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: El Salvador Honey Process Santa Ana
short_desc: Middle roasts call attention to this coffee's impressive body, convincing sweetness, and contrasting low toned cup flavors. Brown sugar, molasses, chocolate-covered nut, creamy mouthfeel. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: El Salvador Miravalle Centroamericano
short_desc: This H1 hybrid from Miravalle farm offers convincing caramel sweetness, with candy-coated walnut and almond marzipan accents, and smoked chocolate chips at darker roast levels. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: El Salvador Santa Ana Pacamara
short_desc: Tart and tannic notes, honey sweetness, black tea with lemon, torrone confections, matcha powder bittering and sweet orange in the aftertaste. A light and bright profile lends itself to pour over brewing. City to City+.

name: Guatemala Acatenango Gesha
short_desc: Complex raw sugar sweetness leads directly into a bouquet of florals, like rose petal poutpourri and star jasmine, with accents of dried tropical fruits, hibiscus tea, sweet lemon, and brisk, tea-like acidity. City to Full City.

name: Guatemala Acatenango Gesha
short_desc: A pristine Gesha cup, resonant sweetness of raw honey accented by notes of Assam tea and rose hips, with tangy orange zest, perfumed with star jasmine, floral lemon, and an aromatic hint of pink bubblegum in the finish. City to City+.

name: Guatemala Acatenango San Diego Buena Vista
short_desc: A balanced flavor profile that's great brewed or as espresso. Dark sugar, caramel, hazelnut, Dutch cocoa, hints of cinnamon and vanilla in the aftertaste, well-integrated acidity. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Antigua Finca Cabrejo
short_desc: Bodied, incredible balance, sugar cane juice, semi-sweet chocolate, top notes of oatmeal cookie with raisin, berry, vanilla aroma, a lemon tea note adds vibrance. Dark roasts are packed with chocolate roast flavors. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Antigua La Parcela Melanie
short_desc: "La Parcela" is in limited supply, promising balanced cup flavors, elegant acidity, raw sugars, almond brittle, molasses, a citrus hint. Full City doubles down on bittersweet chocolates, with a red berry accent note. City to Full City+.

name: Guatemala Antigua Pulcal
short_desc: Convincing brown sugar sweetness backed by fine drinking cocoa, almond flavored syrup, apple-like acidity. Balanced and crowd-pleasing, with dark roasts bringing out chocolate bittersweets en masse. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Antigua Pulcal Inteligente
short_desc: Convincing sweetness, brown sugars, honey bread, Dutch drinking chocolate, tree nuts, and very soft fruited hints. Full City show a more brooding cocoa-roast side. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Antigua Santa Ines
short_desc: The sweetness has a pungent quality, like caramelized sugars with a subtle smoked sweetness, top notes of walnut, marshmallow, some almond marzipan, hazelnut chocolate, well-integrated acidity. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Chimaltenango Tecpan
short_desc: Bright Guatemalan cup when roasted light, fruited hints cut through core flavors of caramel, cocoa, and candied almond. Dark roasts extract flavors of walnut brownie, and dark chocolate almond. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Coban Chichupak Coop
roast: City to Full City+, versatile with moderate acidity in the lighter roasts
short_desc: Approachable, sweet, and moderately complex in the context of other Guatemalas. Bittersweet base flavors, apple accents, well integrated acidity, and chocolate confections through the finish. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Huehuetenango Aguacatones Honey
short_desc: Dark roasts unlock a dense, cocoa-laden profile that's thick and delicious, and stands up to milk too. Not a fruited honey, but flavors of toasted sugar, toffee coated nut, and dark chocolate bittersweets flourish. Full City to Vienna. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Patzun Finca Las Camelias
short_desc: Finca Las Camelias exudes sweet raw sugar flavors, highlighted by fruited notes that crop up along the way. Cane juice, layered bittersweets, with accents of dehydrated strawberry, blackberry, and a winey apple note. City to Full City+.

name: Guatemala San Diego Buena Vista Yellow Bourbon
short_desc: Another sweet, sturdy coffee from San Diego Buena Vista, flavors of caramel, lemon tea with zest, semi-sweet chocolate chips. Surprisingly vibrant in the light roasts. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala San Martin Jilotepeque
cultivar: Bourbon, Bourboncito, Caturra, Catuai, Typica, Catimor, Anacafe 14
short_desc: Crowd-pleasing and balanced, sturdy brown sugar sweetness, chocolate bittersweets, pistachio ice cream, caramelized sugar, and a hint of apple adds to mild perceived acidity. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Producers
short_desc: Moderate sweetness and acidity, base flavors of minimally refined sugars and honey-roasted nut, dried fruit hints, chocolate-covered almond, a berry granola note, and lasting bittersweetness. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Honduras Juan Carlos Sabillon Parainema
short_desc: Exceptional cup clarity, a lovely tart acidity that hints at lemon and white grape, anchored in caramelized sugar sweetness, aromatic hints of lemon balm and pineapple sage, chocolate orange peel. City to Full City.

name: Honduras La Pena Denilson Madrid Parainema
short_desc: Well-defined cup flavors, impactful sweetness, and an herbal tea-like aftertaste. Denilson's coffee shows a vibrant citric side for Honduran coffee, furthered along by a flavor note of lime peel zest. City to City+.

name: Honduras Las Flores Nelson Parainema
short_desc: A personal fave from this year's Honduras coffees, persistent sweetness, big body, herbal aromatics, caramel sauce, citrus accents of lemon water and tangy orange rind, elegant cinnamon note, Mr Pibb soda. City to Full City.

name: Honduras Santa Barbara Jose Esteban
short_desc: Impressive aromatic sweetness, floral like honey, hints of butter-caramel and toasted sugar. Light roasts have a mandarin orange note, while Full City pulls out a juicy grape flavor amidst a chocolatey backdrop. City to Full City.

name: Mexico Chiapas Las Mujeres de Concordia
cultivar: Bourbon, Caturra, Mundo Novo, Typica, Costa Rica 95, Marsellesa, Catimor
short_desc: This coffee offers balanced flavors and roast versatility, sweetness of caramelized sugars, cinnamon, and snickerdoodle cookie. Wisps of cocoa become much more with deeper roasting. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Mexico Chiapas Sierra Mariscal
short_desc: Crowd-pleasing but not too showy, top notes pleasantly restrained amidst a bittersweet backdrop. Molasses, dark cocoa, malted grain, glimpses of fruit when roasted light. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Mexico Comunidad de Coatepec
cultivar: Costa Rica, Marsellesa, Sarchimor, Variedad Colombia
short_desc: Balanced flavors, moderate level of sweetness, chewy body, chocolatey bass tones, molasses and brown sugar, milk chocolate, chocolate-vanilla pinwheel cookie, roasted chesnut, hints of dried fruit. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Mexico Sierra Madre de Chiapas
short_desc: Crowd pleasing and balanced, brown sugar, cream caramel, vanilla pudding, bruleed banana, moderate level of acidity, and tangy roast bittersweets in the darker roasts. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Nicaragua Buenos Aires Los Pinos
short_desc: A crowd pleasing coffee that finds a nice interplay between layers of unrefined sugars, chocolate bittersweets, hints of walnut and pecan, and milder level of acidity. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Nicaragua Dipilto Finca La Laguna
short_desc: Versatility is a strong point, big-body, brown sugars, hazelnut, milder acidity, and bittersweetness ala semi-sweet chocolate chips. Great coffee for milk drinks! City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Nicaragua Dry Process Buenos Aires
short_desc: Rustic fruit and chocolate tones proliferate, along with nutty accents, and hints of aromatic wood, notes of cacao nib, berry, chocolate-covered pistachio, holiday cranberry cookie with pine nut. City+ to Full City+.

name: Nicaragua Dry Process Buenos Aires
short_desc: Quite a unique cup for Central America, elements of stewed and fresh fruit, with a winey edge in the light roast. Cooked prune, fermented orange, whole clove, and an aromatic cedar note. City to Full City.

name: Nicaragua Finca Buenos Aires
short_desc: Always a crowd pleasing brew, Buenos Aires' displays balanced sweetness and low tones, medium body, with notes of cooked brown sugars, chocolate wafer cookie, and chocolate hazelnut spread. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Nicaragua Honey Process San Salvador Java
short_desc: Full City roasts cup a lot like dry process, with dark fruits, cooked blackberry, plum jam, and earth-toned bittersweet chocolates. Body scored 9.8 which bodes well for a long, chocolatey finish. Full City to Full City+.

name: Nicaragua Honey Process San Salvador Java
short_desc: Middle and dark roast range is where this coffee peaks. Dark sugars shift into accents of blackberry and date, earth-toned bittersweetness, foresty aromatics, big body, and milder acidic impression. City+ to Full City+.

name: Nicaragua Jinotega La Bastilla Estate
short_desc: Middle roasts are crowd pleasing with rich bittersweetness, flavors of nougat, roasted nut, chocolate-malted beer grains, cinnamon top note, and a satisfying cocoa powder finish. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Nicaragua Los Altiplanos Java Cultivar
short_desc: A cup with Java cultivar characteristics of herbal aromatics, moderate supporting sweetness and acidity, with accents of demerara sugar, baking spice, spearmint, bell pepper, and tea notes of Sencha and Yerba Mate. City to City+.

name: Panama Boquete La Gloria Estate
short_desc: Another high caliber washed coffee from La Gloria, raw cane sugar, background notes of bittering cacao and almond counter, but never overcome, mouth refreshing acidity, baked apple hint as the coffee cools. City to Full City.

name: Panama Dry Process Carmen Estate
short_desc: Fans of dry process take note, this Panamanian coffee offers a composite of berry flavors and winey aroma, with notes of cranberry, unsulfered apricot, freeze dried strawberry, rustic cocoa power, and pistachio. City to Full City.

name: Panama Paso Ancho Carmen Estate
short_desc: Takes well to light and dark roasting. A nice tight range of flavors such as dark sugars, caramel, chocolate bittersweets, almond biscotti, and dark chocolate-covered macadamia nut. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Carmo de Minas SWP Decaf
short_desc: Sipid sweetness of unrefined sugars fades to balanced roast bittering, with hints of chocolate-covered raisin, sesame chocolate halvah, and substantial body helps make this a crowd pleasing brew. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Coop de Caldas EA Decaf
processing: Wet Process, then Ethyl Acetate Decaf
cultivar: Bourbon, Caturra, Catimor, Variedad Colombia, Typica
short_desc: Very little indication that this coffee is decaf, tart green apple acidity, supporting sweetness of brown sugars, molasses, subtle bake fruits, spiced apple pie filling, fruited cocoa flavor, delicious both light and dark. City to Full City.

name: Costa Rica Helsar SWP Decaf
short_desc: A pleasantly-mild cup profile, clean sweetness, praline nut, apple-like acidic impression (light), rye toast, and cocoa bittersweets when roasted dark. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Costa Rica La Pradera SWP Decaf
