short_desc: Balanced, bittersweet, and with just a touch of acidity, chocolate biscotti, raw sugar , and walnut. Those looking for a daily drinker will get a lot of mileage out of La Pradera! City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Gera-Goma SWP Decaf
processing: Wet and Dry Process, then SWP Decaf
short_desc: This blend of wet and dry process coffees makes a tasty decaf, floral honey sweetness, natural dried apricot, saffron and chicory aromatics, and fruited chocolate flavor when roasted dark. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Geta Bore SWP Decaf
short_desc: Juicy mouthfeel accentuates otherwise subtle hints of red fruit, dried apricot, and Dr Pepper, with ample dark sugar sweetness up front that leads up to a nice sweet finish too. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Guji Gorebeti SWP Decaf
region: Hambela Buliye + Banko Chelchele, Guji Zone
short_desc: A uniquely fruited decaf that shows a lot of origin character and dry process flavors, red fruits reinforce a juicy mouthfeel, notes of stewed peach, baked pear, fruit compote, a hint of pumpernickel. City to City+.

name: Ethiopia Organic Yebuna Terara SWP Decaf
processing: Dry Process + Wet Hulled, then SWP Decaf
type: Farm Gate, Organic/Fair Trade Cert., Decaf
short_desc: The fruity dry process flavors of the pre-decaf coffee come through. Berry notes crop up in the cup, along with bittersweet backing flavors, hints of stewed stone fruits, doughy rye, and rustic sweeteners. City to Full City.

name: Guatemala Cafeteros SWP Decaf
short_desc: Crowd pleasing decaf that's uniquely sweet, simple brown sugars, caramely malted grain, pleasantly mild acidity, and bittersweet side that's well balanced. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Indonesia Nusantara SWP Decaf
processing: Wet Hulled and Honey Labu, the SWP Decaf
short_desc: Nusantara offers balanced bittersweetness, with notes of carob chips, malt syrup, brown bread, an understated note of dark honey, roasted barley tea, big body and a long, chocolate-laden finish. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sweet Maria's Moka Java SWP Decaf Blend
cultivar: Heirloom Cultivars, Abyssinia, Ateng, Tim Tim
short_desc: Moka Java decaf has returned! Bittersweetness meshing with accent notes of cooked fruit and berry, cinnamon-laced sugar, and browned butter, herbaceaus hints. City+ to Full City+. Good espresso.

name: Flores Dry Process Bei Poso Village
short_desc: Bei Poso has syrupy sweetness and body, with bittersweet juice of pink grapefruit, and the pith on the inside of the peel, along with notes of tart salmon berry, and some leathery earth tones in the aftertaste. City to Full City.

name: Flores Gunung Waja Mala
short_desc: Waja Mala has flavors of bran muffin with cinnamon, with notes of turbinado sugar, walnut, a subtle earth tone, the bittersweetness of flourless chocolate torte, and modest level of acidity. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Flores Wolo Wio
short_desc: Middle roasts have no trouble finding a balance of sweetness and low tones, hints of bran muffin, cacao nibs, rustic tobacco, and pleasantly mild acidity. A super versatile coffee! City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Java Dry Process Kuningan Robusta
short_desc: Bittering cocoa, toasted pine nut, savory umami, rye and barley grains, popcorn, a leathery accent, and a unique bitter spice flavor note that's a lot like clove in the finish. Don't forget the punchy caffeine jolt! Full City to French. Nice with a splash of milk!

name: Java Sunda Kawah Kamojang
region: Gunung Mandalawangi and Gunung Kamojang, Garut, West Java
short_desc: Fragrant, clean flavors mark this delightful Javanese coffee, dense brown sugar sweetness, dark tea with honey, lemon spritz, and a mild cocoa presence that's most fully formed in the middle roasts. City to Full City.

name: Java Wet Hulled Waspada
short_desc: Waspada challenges preconceptions you might have about wet hulled coffee. Earthy aspects are accented by unrefined sweeteners, dried date, lemony sour grass, orange herbal bitters, and intense roast bittering. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sulawesi Dry Process Topidi Daeng
short_desc: Topidi Daeng has an earthy sweetness, but the fruits are the more tangible aspect. Wild berry and tropical accents such as strawberry taffy, dried mango, papaya, creamy guava, and a fresh fruit acidic impression. City to Full City.

name: Sulawesi Gowa Desa Topidi
short_desc: Fruit and raw sugars bring to mind apple turnover, along with a tart Bosc or Asian pear notes, aromatic accents of herbal licorice root, balanced bittersweetness, and a tannic black tea flavor that rounds out the finish. City to Full City.*Only 5 bags available!

name: Sulawesi Honey Process Gowa
short_desc: Honey processing highlights body and sweetness in this Sulawesi, wtih a resonant red honey falavor that stretches to the aftertaste, black tea, hints of apple butter, golden plum, persimmon, and a lemon juice accent. City to City+.

name: Sulawesi Wet Hulled Enrekang Rodo Rodo
short_desc: Rustic sweetness compliments an undercurrent of cocoa roast flavors, bittersweet cocoa, sage-infused chocolate, malted grain, rice syrup, palm sugar, and hints of leathery tobacco and banana chips. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sulawesi Wet Hulled Latimojong
short_desc: Litimojong is a high caliber wet hulled coffee, palm and date sugars, rustic earthiness just beneath the surface, intense chocolate roast bittering, herbal aromatics, and a woodsy cedar note. City+ to French. Good for espresso.

name: Sumatra Aceh Bebesen Aulia
short_desc: Intense sweetness and earth toned aroma, rice syrup, palm sugar, traces of tobacco and stewed fruit, bittersweet cocoa, green herbs, woodsy spice notes, and big body. City+ to French. Good for espresso.

name: Sumatra Anaerobic Bebesen Aulia
short_desc: Melds pulpy fruits with earthy wet hulled flavors. Rustic sweetness, lychee, golden date, dried apricot, white wine note. Dark roasts tamp down on fruits, pulling out a bittersweet profile that's slightly fruited. City+ to Full City+.

name: Sumatra Dry Process Kerinci Pendekar
region: Gunung Tujuh and Kayu Aro, Mount Kerinci
short_desc: Atypical flavor profile for Sumatra, with complex fruit flavors like freeze dried berry, fig jam, date paste, and dried tamarind, with earth toned cocoa, sarsaparilla, creamy body, and aromatic wood note in the finish. City+ to Full City+.

name: Sumatra Dry Process Ribang Gayo
cultivar: Abyssinia, Ateng, Gayo 1, Gayo 2, Tim Tim
short_desc: Dry processing has quite an impact on flavors, spiced fruitcake aromatics, fermented banana, cherry, berry reductions, prune, pine, dusky peat, tarragon, granola, chocolate roast flavors, and coconut pulp. City+ to Full City+.

name: Sumatra Honey Labu Kerinci Pendekar
region: Gunung Tujuh and Kayu Aro, Mount Kerinci
processing: Honey Process, then Wet Hulled (Giling Basah)
short_desc: This uniquely processed coffee offers some of the typical earth-toned flavors of Sumatran coffee, along with herbal Manuka honey, pulpy fruits, fresh tarragon, aromatic cedar, and bittersweet low tones. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sumatra Honey Process Bebesen Aulia
short_desc: Honey processing makes for such a unique Sumatra coffee, dark honey, date sugar, dried fruit, bittering cocoa, notes of chocolate coated raisin, herbal accents, and traces of tannic tea. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sumatra Kerinci Pendekar Coop
short_desc: Exemplary wet hulled coffee, intense cup flavors, rustic sorghum syrup, earth-toned hints, baked apple accent, bittersweet roast tones, malted grain, smokey peat and baking cocoa finish. City+ to French. Good for espresso.

name: Sumatra Lintong Mutu Batak
short_desc: Earth-toned sweetness, rustic date and palm sugars, pungent bittersweetness, raw cacao, sharp tobacco, peat/scotch aromatic accent, inky thick body, licorice hint. City+ to French. Good for espresso.

name: Sumatra Lintong Pak Joner
short_desc: Complex earth tones and intense bittersweetness of high % cacao bar and bakers chocolate, accents of rustic palm sugar, peat-like scotch note, tobacco, leathery sweetness, aromatic cedar, and an orange oil hint. City+ to French.

name: Sumatra Ribang Gayo
roast: City to Full City+ - incredibly versatile Sumatra
short_desc: Intense sweetenss of palm sugar and dark fruits, muscat grape, fermented blackberry, sweet tobacco, aromatic cedar, and waves of bittersweetness when roasted dark. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sumatra Spice-Aged Lintong
processing: Wet Hulled (Giling Basah), then Spice-Aged for 36 months
roast: City+ is a good starting point to experience the strong spice flavors, but it shows well up to Full City+
short_desc: A coffee aged for 36 months inside bags with whole anise, clove, and cardamom. The flavors are so intense, mulling spices (in a BIG way), black pepper, caramel sweetness, aromatic wood, and brothy savory-spiced notes. No actual spices are in the final product, but you'd guess there were based on flavor! City+ to Full City+.*Limit of 1 lb. per customer in order to spread this small, unique Sumatra lot to as many people as possible!

name: Sumatra Wet Process Ribang Gayo
cultivar: Abyssinia, Ateng, Gayo 1, Gayo 2, Tim Tim
short_desc: A Sumatra with balanced flavors and moderate acidity relative to the region, toasted sugar overtones, apple hint, sweet squash with brown sugar, and sage-infused chocolate when roasted dark. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Timor Leste Dry Process Daurfusu
short_desc: A wild and wooly cup profile both fruited and sweet, flavors of fermented apple cider, mango puree, earth-toned date, Bartlett pear with some pear skin bittering, and body so thick you could stand a cupping spoon in it! City to Full City+.

name: Timor Leste Dry Process Lulirema
short_desc: Fruited and earth-toned sweetness, notes of strawberry milk powder, cooked rhubarb, coconut palm sugar, dark corn syrup, fig, and rustic chocolate when roasted dark. Incredible body to boot. City+ to Full City+.

name: Timor Leste Dukurai Daurfusu
short_desc: A sweet undercurrent, subtle fruited hints of raisin, red apple, and peach skin, with dark roasts pulling out intense roast bittering, German chocolate cake, and smokey cacao nibs. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Timor Leste Ermera Fatu Besi
short_desc: Fatu Besi is a mild acid cup, with a sort of smokey sweetness ala dark corn syrup, roasted cacao bittering, caramel Cracker Jacks, and capable of developing robust roast flavors. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Timor Leste Honey Process Daurfusu
short_desc: Fruits have a quiet presence in the cup profile, accents of dried natural apricot and pear are wrapped in  bittersweet hot cocoa, unrefined sugars, with a hint of spiced tea in the background. City to Full City.

name: Timor Leste Lekisala
short_desc: Caramel sweetness consolidates nicely with a flavor profile of Hershey's chocolate bar and cocoa rice crispies, with mild green apple acidic impression. Versatile and balanced! City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Timor Leste Taurema
short_desc: Middle roasts tie together unrefined sweetness, roast bittering, and savory nut tones, with cup flavors hinting at  nougat, pistachio, tobacco leaf, amaretto, and Bakers chocolate. Great with a splash of milk! City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Papua New Guinea Kainantu Sero
short_desc: Date sugar, blackstrap molasses, hints of dried fig, sticky rice pudding, pine oil and palo santo stick, citrus rind, and dark roasts draw out more crowd-pleasing bittersweetness. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Papua New Guinea Korgua Peaberry
short_desc: Raw sugar flavors at the front of the cup, molasses, and rapidura, with subtle hints of prune, raisin, and tannic dark black tea. Sweetness stands tall in dark roasts too! City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Papua New Guinea Korgua X
short_desc: Medium body across a range of roasts, and moderate acidity, fruited lemongrass hint, dried apple slices, natural dried stone fruit flavor, with some rustic sweetness at a shade more roast development. City to Full City.

name: Papua New Guinea Kuta Waghi
short_desc: Brews very well at City+, torched sugar, toffee, understated hints of prune, and dried citrus peel, aromatic tobacco, ample bittering that points to tannic tea, and unsweetened baking chocolate. City+ to Full City+.

name: Brazil Adair Oliveira Neto
short_desc: Atypical Brazil dry process, pleasant flavors of simple brown sugars are propped up by mild apple-like acidity, a crisp Bartlett pear note, and subtle sweet herbals add an aromatic quality to the cup. City to Full City.

name: Brazil Alta Mogiana Bom Jesus
short_desc: Bittersweet bass notes flow through cup, accented by hints of peanut taffy, cocoa powder, and dark chocolate covered nut. Espresso shots are creamy, with richness and depth of flourless torte. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Canastra Luis Otavio
short_desc: Delicious Brazil cup with moderate sweetness, nutty hints, hazelnut syrup, caramel, chocolate malted grain, and intense bittersweetness and body in the darker roasts. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Carmo Fazenda Furnas
short_desc: Notes of molasses and banana nut breads, barley malt, bittersweet chocolate, low acidity, creamy mouthfeel, and hints of dried fruit in the background. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Cerrado Fred Terumi
short_desc: What a great body coffee this is, moderate caramel and toasted sugar sweetness, high % cacao bar and baking chocolate bass tones. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso, and perfect base espresso component!

name: Brazil Dry Process Cafeicultores de Minas
short_desc: Intense roast bittering underscores flavors of baking chocolate, nutty notes, sesame, a hint of amaretto and low acidity. Great for milk drinks! Full City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Dry Process Ipanema Farm
region: Conceicao do Rio Verde, Minas Gerais
short_desc: A hefty bodied coffee with an array of flavors that include cocoa powder, hazelnut, almond flour, accents of stewed and freeze dried fruits, and Baker's cocoa finish. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Fazenda Alta Vista
short_desc: Culmination of roasted nut and cocoa bittering aspects, burned caramel, almond and pecan, hazelnut chocolate, chocolate dipped almond brittle, and a hint of apple butter. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Ipanema Yellow Bourbon
region: Conceicao do Rio Verde, Minas Gerais
short_desc: A pleasantly restrained coffee with low acidity and big body, flavors of chocolate and almond milks, walnut, and dark cocoa. Roast versatility is a strong point. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Mogiana Vera Lucia
short_desc: A profile that lends itself to milk drinks, opaque bittersweet backdrop, mild nutty sweetness, notes of almond extract, baking cocoa, banana-nut bread, and some earthy spice in the finish. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Patrocinio Fazenda Escalada
short_desc: Body and bittersweetness are central to the cup profile, notes of sticky natural sweeteners like sorghum syrup and molasses, peanut butter cookie, and lasting chocolate roast tones. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Pulp Natural Fazenda IP
short_desc: Bittersweet cacao notes are balanced by flavors of burnt sugar, barley malt, corn syrup, and a pleasant bittering of baking chocolate in the aftertaste. Very versatile Brazil. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Buesaco EA Decaf
short_desc: Difficult to peg this coffee as decaf. Caramel in flavor and aroma, cinnamon pinwheel cookie, dried apple, chocolate-banana hint, and moderate acidity level for decaf. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Cresta El Hato
short_desc: The combination of unrefined sweetness and baking spice flavors in my City+ roast conjured a mental picture of snickerdoodle cookies, along with hints of molasses, panela, and delicious dark cocoa notes. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Honey Process Aponte
short_desc: Bold bittersweet aroma, rustic chocolate, roasted cacao nibs, subtle hints of berry, fermented cherry, dried dates, along with a toasted grain bittering that adds an umami aspect. City+ to French. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Honey Process Aponte
short_desc: Both light and darker roasts are delicious, with molasses sweetness and moderate roast tones intertwined with fruited accents of stewed apple, pear butter, dried date, fruit leather and apple spice tea. Bittersweet City to Full City.

name: Colombia Honey Process Cristian Martinez
short_desc: Heavy-handed cup profile that touches on winey fruits and rustic sweetness. Prune juice, apples cooked with cinnamon, plum wine, stewed cherries with some skin bittering, and cocoa bittersweetness that lingers. City to Full City.

name: Colombia Honey Process El Paramo
processing: Honey Process - the green looks a bit rustic, with a few dark/discolored beans mixed in - see Farm Notes
short_desc: Freighted with unrefined sugars and bracing bittersweetness, hints of rice syrup, molasses, dried cherry, tamarind, Lipton tea, and light berry aroma. An incredibly bodied cup. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Inza Anibal Pillimue
short_desc: Anibal's coffee is an absolute treat as pour over, floral sugarcane juice accented by fruit flavors that have a winey ripeness, white peach, apricot, red apple, and a plum note that feeds into an elegant acidic impression. City to City+.*available in 1 lb. bags only due to limited quantity

name: Colombia Inza Julian Piedra
short_desc: Pronounced sweetness across our recommended roast range, with flavors ranging from raw honey, to toasted sugars, golden raisin, blackberry, along with creamy body and fruited acidic impression. City to Full City.

name: Colombia Inza Luis Hernan
region: Vereda Alto de la Cruz, Inza, Cauca
short_desc: While it starts off restrained, Luis Hernan's coffee opens up to show some brighter fruit notes of apple and berry tea, enhanced by a sweetness that denotes raw brown sugars. Great Colombia for pour-over brewing. City to Full City.

name: Colombia Inza Rafael Rivas
short_desc: A moderately sweet cup, with chewy chocolate, sponge cake, caramel drizzled almonds, and aroma of sundae toppings like hot fudge, caramel sauce, and candied pecans. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Inza Rio Paez
short_desc: A bittersweet brew with muted top notes, the underlying sweetness more profuse with each sip. Notes of unrefined sugar, chocolate-coconut, walnut, soft shades of dried fruit. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Inza Vereda Guanacas
short_desc: Flavor notes from complex sugars to clean fruited hints, like apple, Monukka raisin, dried fig, pumpkin pie with whipping cream, and a honeyed flavor that hangs on in the aftertaste. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Inza Vereda San Antonio
short_desc: Very attractive sweetness light and dark roasted, vanilla caramels, honey, chocolate-caramel-coconut cookie, an apple note that boosts acidity, and a hint of a blackberry fruit reduction. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Narino Vereda Buesaco
short_desc: Flavor profiles of raw sugars and fruit accents, an aromatic note of butterscotch, blackberry, plum, and some orange peel bittering. Full City adds in a ribbon of cacao/chocolate bar, and dark berry hint. City to Full City+.

name: Colombia Narino Vereda San Miguel
short_desc: Vereda San Miguel impresses with clean cup sweetness of raw honey and panela sugar, accented by fruited hints of pear, apple-cinnamon cake, and syrupy stone fruits. Moderate acidity adds a liveliness to the light roasts too. City to Full City.

name: Colombia Pavon Finca Los Palomos
short_desc: Always an absolute treat to taste, Palomos has complex raw sugars, glimpses of apricot juice, dried cherry, ripe plum, citrus zest, bracing black tea in the lighter roasts. Excellent choice for pour-over brew! City to Full City.

name: Colombia Paez Rio Chiquito
short_desc: Almond/nut hints are tucked under a nice base sweetness, with flavor profiles of butter caramels, molasses, candied almond, pecan cookie, toffee-coated nut, and some bittersweet intensity. City to Full City+. Excels as espresso.

name: Colombia Rio Chiquito Don Luis
short_desc: A sweet profile of "blondie" caramel/butterscotch bars, lemongrass herbal note, tart apple adds to the acidic impression, and a balanced bittersweet side comes with roast. City to Full City+.

name: Colombia Tolima China Alta
short_desc: A real shape shifter, smells of complex sugars transform to delicious fruits in the brew! Brown sugar, baked apple, cinnamon, raisin, and a squirt of citrus. Full City yields dark chocolate with red berry hints. City to Full City.

name: Colombia Tolima Edward Sandoval Heirloom Bourbon
roast: City to City+ - light roasts highlight the aromatic cup characteristics
short_desc: A competition-level heirloom Bourbon ("Chiroso") in limited quantity. Aromatic sweetness,  refined fruits, and sparkling acidity, floral raw sugars, apple, Bartlett pear, white grape, cinnamon-apple tea. City to City+.*limited to 1# per customer

name: Colombia Tolima Santa Rita
short_desc: Convincing sweetness at a wide range of roasts made it hard to choose a favorite! Panela sugar, juicy body, brown sugar and cinnamon streusel, dark fruit hints, and restrained malic acidity. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Urrao Heirloom Caturra
short_desc: This heirloom Caturra (aka "Chiroso") from Urrao produces a uniquely aromatic cup, with rounded sweetness, pink grapefruit, and perfumed highlights of lemon tea, red rooibos, chamomile, and coffee fruit cascara tea. City to Full City.

name: Colombia Veredas Vecinas
short_desc: Impressive cup sweetness and body at most roast levels, honey accents, pistachio torrone, and nougat, with a faint apple hint. Dark roasts boost deep chocolate low tones perfect for brew or espresso. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Veredas Vecinas
region: Inza, Cauca + Anaime, Cajamarca + Urrao, Antioquia
short_desc: Nougat sweetness, pistachio torrone, aromatic honey, red apple top note, big body, fruited acidic impression, and dark roasts boost deep chocolate low tones perfect for brew or espresso. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Peru Bello Horizonte Andres Burga
region: Bello Horizonte, San Jose De Lourdes, San Ignacio
short_desc: This Peru ticks off so many boxes for me! Saccharine sweetness, fruited overtones, moderate acidity level, notes of brown sugar, Thompson raisins, apples with cinnamon, and tea-like accents of Earl Grey and PG Tips. City to Full City.

name: Peru Bello Horizonte Andres Burga
region: Bello Horizonte, San Jose De Lourdes, San Ignacio
short_desc: This Peru ticks off so many boxes for me! Profuse brown sugar sweetness and moderate acidity for Peru, subtle hints of Thompson raisin, orange, spiced apple and tea-like accents when roasted light. City to Full City.

name: Peru El Diamante Roger Chilcon
region: El Diamante, San Jose de Lourdes
short_desc: Refined sweetness of minimally-processed sugars, fruit flavors have some bearing on profile, notes of cranberry-apple juice, clove spiced cider in aroma, dried date, drinking chocolate, and milky body. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Peru El Paraiso Yoner Arevalo
short_desc: Some similar flavor characteristics of dry process coffee, fruited hints of cherimoya, cooked plantains, banana bread, red cherry, along with creamy chestnut, and prominent chocolate bittersweetness. City+ to Vienna.

name: Peru Finca San Fernando Gesha
roast: City to City+ - keep it light for floral highlights and brighter cup characteristics
short_desc: This tiny 2 bag Gesha lot from Finca San Fernando made a big impression on us when roasted light: a delicate jasmine note, tannic black tea, dried apple and apricot, and refreshing lemon-like acidic impression. City to City+.*due to the limited stock we are only offering 1 lb. bags

name: Peru Las Pirias Ramiro Vela
short_desc: Refined sweetness, minimally processed sugars like turbinado, along with hints of honey, yellow cherry, apple, and aromatic note of spiced cider. Full City+ roasts have bittersweet SMORE, and light fruit accent. City to Full City+.

name: Sumatra Raja Batak Peaberry
short_desc: Classic Lintong character, coconut palm sugar sweetness is accented by rooty earth notes, peat, tobacco, leather, cedar, cacao, and sage, and viscous body leads to a long aftertaste. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sweet Maria's Ethiopiques Version 2.0
short_desc: A velvety textured shot, bittersweet and fruited, with a long lasting finish. Notes of blackberry, stewed fruits, chocolate-covered plum, Scharffen Berger bar, and creamy ganache. Best to rest 48+ hours after roasting. Full City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sweet Maria's Half-Caff Blend
processing: Wet and Dry Process, then SWP Decaf
short_desc: A blend of 1/3 regular to 2/3 decaf for those looking for all the flavor with only a sliver of the caffeine jolt. Bittersweetness at the front of the cup, low acid, and medium body, with a note of carob. Full City to Full City+.

name: Sweet Maria's Polar Expresso Holiday Blend
short_desc: Roll out the holiday cheer with our limited edition Polar Expresso blend! Velvety-textured shot that extracts dark chocolate low tones that are syrupy and delicious, accented by a lemony bright spot, berry fruit hints, and subtle spiced aroma. Full City to Full City+. Fantastic espresso!
